Whatever the hardest trade that my fellow contributor Cody Willard answered with was often the best and most profitable trade. So... "Hey Cody, what's the hardest trade?" Cody Willard is no longer writing for TheStreet (but I will tweet this out so hopefully he will answer it).

In his absence, I will try to answer the question myself: In my view the hardest trade is to stay with (and not sell) the stocks that were recently purchased and have had reasonably large percentage gains in the last few trading sessions.

Wait, on reflection, the hardest trade might be buying stocks after the large advance. And buying now may pay even greater dividends for the intermediate-term investor -- and, maybe even, for the short-term trader. It's the hardest trade. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC
